step_data.thought: I'm looking at a product inventory page in the Magento Admin panel. I notice that the page currently has a search filter applied for 'Maya Tunic' and shows '0 records found'. This means there are no products matching that search term. To find the product with the lowest stock quantity, I need to clear this filter first and view all products. Then I can sort by the Quantity column to see which product has the lowest stock. I see there's a button to clear the filter with bid '948', which has the text '\\ue620'.
